This is a reference to the novelization of the film Robin Hood: Prince of Thieves starring Kevin Kosner of Waterworld fame, who is himself based on a character from Brooklyn 99, TV's Kevin Kozner.
This is a reference to the novelization of the animated movie Watership Down, which is a sequel to the novelization of the 2006 film Charlotte's Web, starring Steve Buscemi.

This is a reference to the novelization of the music Hades Town, which is inspired by the Sarah Bareilles musical Waitress, which is an adaptation of the novelization of the film Waitress starring Keri Russell.
This song is about the novelization of the 1918 musical Sinbad, which itself is a reference to the 2003 film Sinbad: Legend of the Seven Seas.
This is a reference to the "fake empire" that exists in Star Wars and the second reference to the novelization of The Star Wars Holiday Special on this list.
This is a reference to the novelization of the Saturday Night Live skit "More Cowbell".

Based solely on the line "A giant rat that's nibbling on my pride," this song is a reference to the novelization of the film Charlotte's Web from 2006, starring Steve Buscemi as a large rat known only as Templeton, who devours an entire carnival whole and then sings a song about it. This is a reference to the novelization of 1940 film The Grapes of Wrath, which is itself inspired by the 1982 film Star Trek 2: The Wrath of Kahn, whose screenplay was loosely based on the 2022 viral TikTok hit, "Corn."
